1 unit(s) Halloumi Cheese
7 g Shawarma Spice Blend
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
2 unit(s) Flatbread
7 g Parsley
2 unit(s) Green Onion
1 unit(s) Lemon
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Lettuce
2 tbsp Tahini Sauce
1 unit(s) Tomato
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
½ tsp Salt*
½ tsp Pepper*
½ tsp Sugar*
3 tbsp Oil*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 425 °F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Mince or grate garlic.
Juice half the lemon. Cut remaining lemon into wedges.
In a large bowl, stir together tahini, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) lemon juice, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and garlic.

Cut flatbreads into 1-inch pieces.
On a parchment-lined baking sheet, add flatbread pieces and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with half (all for 4 ppl) the Shawarma Spice Blend and pepper, then toss to coat.
Bake in the top of the oven for 7-9 min, until golden and crispy.

In a large non-stick pan, heat 1 tbsp oil over medium-high.
Cut halloumi into 3/4-inch cubes, then rinse and pat dry with paper towels.
Add halloumi to pan. (NOTE: Cook in batches for 4 servings, using 1 tbsp oil per batch.) Cook for 3-4 min, turning occasionally, until golden. Remove pan from heat.

Cut tomato into 1/2-inch pieces.
Thinly slice green onions.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut cucumber in half lengthwise, then chop into 1/2-inch pieces.
Roughly chop parsley.
Remove and discard outer layer of lettuce. Remove stem. Cut lettuce into quarters, then chop into 1/2-inch pieces.

To the bowl with dressing, add tomatoes, green onions, peppers, cucumber, lettuce and half the parsley. Toss to combine.
Add crispy flatbread pieces and toss again. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad evenly between plates. Top with halloumi.
Sprinkle remaining parsley over top.
Serve with a lemon wedge.